Use table properties to control a table's appearance.

Display Totals and Subtotals

Measure functions are calculated according to all data in the relevant subgrouping. For example, the Total of Max Annual Revenue returns the maximum annual revenue of the entire column. If the formula for the column is A/B, the subtotal is the subtotal of A/subtotal of B.

Totals and subtotals work by using the rollup statement to calculate totals of grouped data. For more information on the functionality and limitations of totals and subtotals, refer to the rollup section of the group topic in the Analytics SAQL Developer Guide.

Choose a Table Theme

Click a theme to apply it to a table.

Set the Spacing for Columns and Rows

To increase or decrease the whitespace in all cells, click a Cell Padding tile. To set column width, select an option from the Column Width dropdown menu, then enter a value or values in Width in Pixels.

Set Header Row Style

For the header row, you can set the cell background color, and the color and font size for text.

Add an Index Column to Values Tables

To add or remove an index column from a values table, click Show Row Index Column. Include reps' Chatter profile pictures next to their KPIs in leaderboards. Or, add flags to your compare table showing worldwide sales data.
title: Customizing Tables in Salesforce Analytics
